   "source": [
    "# Scripting landmark warps\n",
    "\n",
    "Landmark warping can be scripted using the **mwarp1d.warp_landmark** function.\n",
    "\n",
    "Let’s first run an example script then consider the details:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "import mwarp1d\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "#define a plotting function (for re-use below)\n",
    "def plot_warp_results(y, yw, x0, x1):\n",
    "    plt.figure()\n",
    "    ax    = plt.axes()\n",
    "    c0,c1 = 'blue', 'orange'\n",
    "    ax.plot(y,  color=c0, label='Original')\n",
    "    ax.plot(yw, color=c1, label='Warped')\n",
    "    [ax.plot(xx, y[xx],  'o', color=c0)  for xx in x0]\n",
    "    [ax.plot(xx, yw[xx], 'o', color=c1)    for xx in x1]\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('Domain position  (%)', size=13)\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('Dependent variable value', size=13)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "#define landmarks:\n",
    "Q    = 101       #domain size\n",
    "x0   = [38, 63]  #initial landmark location(s)\n",
    "x1   = [25, 68]  #final landmark location(s)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "#apply warp:\n",
    "y    = np.sin( np.linspace(0, 4*np.pi, Q) )  #an arbitary 1D observation\n",
    "yw   = mwarp1d.warp_landmark(y, x0, x1)      #warped 1D observation\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "#plot:\n",
    "plot_warp_results(y, yw, x0, x1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The input arguments to warp_landmark include:\n",
    "\n",
    "* **y** — the 1D data to be warped\n",
    "* **x0** — initial landmark positions\n",
    "* **x1** — final landmark positions\n",
    "\n",
    "Let’s consider what happens when only a single landmark is specified:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x0   = [38]\n",
    "x1   = [25]\n",
    "yw   = mwarp1d.warp_landmark(y, x0, x1)\n",
    "plot_warp_results(y, yw, x0, x1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note that using a single landmark causes the entire domain to be warped.\n",
    "\n",
    "To restrict warping effects to a local area, add more landmarks, like this:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x0   = [12, 38, 63]\n",
    "x1   = [12, 25, 63]\n",
    "yw   = mwarp1d.warp_landmark(y, x0, x1)\n",
    "plot_warp_results(y, yw, x0, x1)"
   ]
  }
